verbose_text: We observed that cell viability, as evaluated using CCK-8, significantly improved with both alpha- and beta-antithrombin in a dose dependent manner, while cellular injury, as measured using the LDH level, was significantly suppressed only by a high dose of beta-antithrombin.
evidence: injury, as measured using the LDH level, was significantly suppressed only by a high dose of beta-antithrombin
